eck the `AbstractSshWagon` class to understand how `createZip` functions. This could clarify whether directories are included in its output. It's essential to ensure I have a complete picture of what this code does!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Pb7pYBUNrnIgrjBnvHQ9hOSV|fc_08d439654ac7d04b016a03af453914819c91cc1a867b17c22b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nurl='https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/wagon/wagon-ssh-common/1.0-beta-2/wagon-ssh-common-1.0-beta-2-sources.jar'\ntry:\n data=urllib.request.urlopen(url,timeout=10).read(); open('/tmp/wagon-ssh-common-sources.jar','wb').write(data); print(len(data))\nexcept Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY\nrm -rf /tmp/wagon-common-src && mkdir /tmp/wagon-common-src && cd /tmp/wagon-common-src && jar xf /tmp/wagon-ssh-common-sources.jar && rg -n \"createZip|class AbstractSshWagon|getFileList|resourceExists\" /tmp/wagon-common-src", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 661, "output": 1270, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29579, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778626353386, "responseId": "resp_08d439654ac7d04b016a03af32095c819ca0526fb10b5a74d7"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Pb7pYBUNrnIgrjBnvHQ9hOSV|fc_08d439654ac7d04b016a03af453914819c91cc1a867b17c22b", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "23820\n/tmp/wagon-common-src/org/apache/maven/wagon/providers/ssh/AbstractSshWagon.java:52:public abstract class AbstractSshWagon\n/tmp/wagon-common-src/org/apache/maven/wagon/providers/ssh/AbstractSshWagon.java:308:            createZip( files, zipFile, sourceDirectory );\n/tmp/wagon-common-src/org/apache/maven/wagon/providers/ssh/AbstractSshWagon.java:346:    public List getFileList( String destinationDirectory )\n/tmp/wagon-common-src/org/